@midnightmoon_15  I think it's possible that they might. Bad Clue was in 2020, and in 2021 Ego was a spinoff of the genre. Then Bad Clue II happened in 2022, and Grudge as a spiritual successor to Ego happened in 2023. So if the pattern continues, Bad Clue III could be in 2024.
Of course though next year will have the big E-word elephant in the room and it's hard to say how that will affect things, only that it certainly will. GoSe has its own production team though so it might actually be less affected than SVT's other schedules.

author: @anggunpelangi4866
text: Thank you so much Seventeen and Going Team! I was feeling super down and super stressed while I was writing my Thesis to earn my degree, but then I stumbled upon Seventeen and Going Seventeen, and it helped me a looooot! I began binge-watching the episodes while slowly gaining the energy to continue writing (I watched it during breaks since I have to read the translations cause I do not speak korean, and playing Seventeen's song while writing!) and I finally finished it. To me, Going Team and Seventeen are very precious and have a special place in my heart! 2 Months being a baby carat and a cubic now ❣ I hope all the best for Going Team, Seventeen and the Team behind Seventeen as well! Take a good care, stay healthy, stay warm, don't forget to rest when it's starting to get overwhelming🥺 My wednesdays are surely going to be quite empty and kinda dull now BUT I think it's time to watch the rest of the GoSe I haven't watched and re-watching all of them till we meet again next year! Again, no words can actually explain how grateful and thankful I am to find you🥰 Once again, thank you so much for never disappointing us and being our happy pills as always🥰

author: @sonalisamal2009
text: What a beautiful send-off episode to Going Seventeen 2023. I really loved all the past content (as I'm binge watching them) and everything that was filmed this year. Thank you for giving us amazing, thrilling, hilarious, interesting and wholesome content. So much versatility. Variety kings for real. It would definitely feel like a part of our life is missing when we'll not get anymore Going Seventeen content this year, but we can still watch the previous episodes again to fill that time and have that feeling of joy that Seventeen gives us. I'm really excited and looking forward to next year's Going Seventeen. Till then, lots of love to the GoSe team. You guys are the coolest and most humourous people. Also, lots of love to Seventeen always, and sending you best wishes for the tour and concert. SCoups, get well, take care of yourself, we miss you. Other Seventeen members in Japan, also stay healthy. You guys are our healing. And, last but not the least, I wish all Carats good health, happiness, peace and love. Let's grow well together. Let's keep supporting Seventeen and try to be respectful and not let anyone tarnish the image of the members or our fandom. More power to everyone ❤
